  "text": "The outer integument initiation at the chalaza is the first morphological evidence that adaxial-abaxial polarity establishment has occurred, and the radially symmetrical primordium has switched to bilateral development [CITATION_1] . At this developmental stage, which corresponds to the BN stage of microspores, the ovule assumes the anatropous position. The micropyle, faced downward and placed near the base of the funiculus (Fig. 5f, g ), represents the ovule developmental stage named as stage V.",
